    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-10-11T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-10-11T13:00:00-05:00" n="1499"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1499">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 855.48/322</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_PWH1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Page</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the</hi>
                    <gloss type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Secretary of State</hi>
                    </gloss>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-10-11T18:00:00+00:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 11, 1915, 6 p. m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 8.15 p. m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2986. My 2736, September 3, and your 2088, September 9, 5 p. m., and September
                    13, p. m.<note n="1" xml:id="d1499fn1">Instruction of September 13 not
                        printed.</note> The plan is scotched apparently for good by objections from
                    the French Government.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">American Ambassador</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
